WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.337
[♪ pop music playing]

00:45.254 --> 00:48.966
PERFECT CROWN

00:59.851 --> 01:00.978
THIS IS A WORK OF FICTION

01:01.061 --> 01:02.980
CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
WERE FILMED SAFELY

01:03.063 --> 01:04.564
[♪ inspiring music playing]

01:17.202 --> 01:18.203
Seong Huiju!

01:19.663 --> 01:20.831
Come on out now.

01:37.472 --> 01:38.557
Seong Huiju!

01:39.224 --> 01:41.435
-Just give me a second!
-[music stops abruptly]

01:41.935 --> 01:44.563
Don't you find him to be so impatient?

01:44.646 --> 01:47.441
Ah. He is generally of
a most easygoing disposition. [chuckles]

01:47.524 --> 01:48.900
[I-AN] We're late!

01:48.984 --> 01:51.028
-Why that…
-No, Your Ladyship! [chuckles]

01:53.071 --> 01:54.448
[sighs] My apologies.

01:57.326 --> 01:58.910
Yes, please check the seat number for me.

01:58.994 --> 01:59.995
-Thank you.
-[sighs]

02:01.997 --> 02:04.624
Wait, is Ms. Seong still getting dressed?

02:04.708 --> 02:06.293
She must be sewing the gown herself.

02:06.793 --> 02:08.795
She could've made two by now.

02:09.588 --> 02:10.589
Seong Huiju!

02:13.300 --> 02:15.010
Well, at this rate…

02:15.093 --> 02:16.637
[♪ dreamy music playing]

02:20.891 --> 02:24.019
PERFECT CROWN

02:24.811 --> 02:25.896
EPISODE 6

02:25.979 --> 02:29.900
Her Majesty said your attendance
would not be required.

02:29.983 --> 02:32.402
Uncle insisted I be there.

02:33.195 --> 02:34.363
His Royal Highness did?

02:34.946 --> 02:35.947
Yes.

02:40.369 --> 02:41.370
[crickets chirping]

02:42.162 --> 02:43.205
[exhales sharply]

02:48.460 --> 02:49.461
Your Majesty.

02:53.215 --> 02:54.299
You came.

02:54.383 --> 02:57.886
How could I refuse a request
from the Queen Mother?

03:06.395 --> 03:08.438
[♪ classical dance music playing]

03:17.989 --> 03:20.617
Announcing Her Majesty the Queen Mother.

03:20.701 --> 03:22.285
[♪ string ensemble stops playing]
STYLE
::cue()

04:00.490 --> 04:02.951
Thank you for inviting me, Your Majesty.

04:03.910 --> 04:07.122
I would've been most delighted
to have been invited to the reception too.

04:07.205 --> 04:08.415
It is such a shame…

04:12.085 --> 04:13.420
[stammers]

04:13.503 --> 04:15.088
Forgive me, Your Majesty.

04:18.175 --> 04:20.135
I hope you enjoy the banquet.

04:29.144 --> 04:31.563
How would you find her
as Grand Prince I-AN's consort?

04:38.195 --> 04:40.864
She is neither too remarkable
nor of too humble a station.

04:41.698 --> 04:43.283
Is she not quite suitable?

04:45.410 --> 04:47.454
[attendant] Announcing Grand Prince I-AN.

04:51.792 --> 04:53.293
[♪ dreamy music playing]

05:41.091 --> 05:42.259
[♪ music ends]

05:48.390 --> 05:50.392
[♪ string ensemble resumes playing]

06:35.270 --> 06:37.105
It was a request from I-AN.

06:39.733 --> 06:42.611
It seems he wishes to leave her
a handsome parting gift.

06:45.447 --> 06:46.656
We must honor his wishes.

06:50.535 --> 06:52.537
So there is a use for this after all.

06:53.246 --> 06:54.664
[Huiju] Don't you dance this often?

06:55.457 --> 06:57.208
I hated these lessons the most.

06:57.792 --> 06:58.793
[chuckles]

06:59.502 --> 07:00.503
[whispers] Me too.

07:01.046 --> 07:02.047
[chuckles]

07:10.430 --> 07:11.806
[guests murmuring]

07:19.689 --> 07:20.899
Even so,

07:21.483 --> 07:22.817
this seems quite effective.

07:23.818 --> 07:25.028
Everyone's eyes are on us.

07:37.582 --> 07:39.000
You should only have eyes for me.

07:40.502 --> 07:43.004
As if we were hopelessly in love.

07:45.632 --> 07:48.385
I hear you, but this won't be enough.

07:48.468 --> 07:49.594
I know.
STYLE
::cue()

08:01.648 --> 08:03.358
-[♪ music ends]
-[applauding]

08:15.370 --> 08:16.496
Follow my lead.

08:24.087 --> 08:25.839
[guests gasping, whispering]

08:36.474 --> 08:38.393
[guest 1] Wait,
don't tell me that ring is…

08:38.476 --> 08:40.061
[guest 2] Is that Queen UIHYEON's ring?

08:40.937 --> 08:42.647
[guest 3] Gosh, she's so lucky.

08:44.691 --> 08:46.109
[whispers] Your Royal Highness.

08:48.528 --> 08:49.904
Compared to you…

08:52.032 --> 08:53.700
my pace may seem much slower.

08:56.661 --> 08:57.787
Even so…

09:01.124 --> 09:02.834
will you give me your hand in marriage?

09:02.917 --> 09:04.335
[guests chattering]

09:07.130 --> 09:08.339
[♪ joyful music playing]

09:14.679 --> 09:17.390
-[guests applauding]
-[fireworks exploding]

10:21.579 --> 10:22.580
Your Majesty.

10:24.374 --> 10:25.416
Will you honor us

10:26.584 --> 10:27.836
with your royal blessing?

10:29.087 --> 10:30.088
[exhales deeply]

10:30.171 --> 10:31.422
[breathes shakily]

10:37.262 --> 10:38.596
[♪ music stops]

10:40.306 --> 10:41.307
Your Majesty.

10:50.900 --> 10:52.277
You have my blessing.

10:53.153 --> 10:54.863
[♪ joyful music resumes]

10:58.658 --> 11:00.660
I wish you great happiness, Uncle.

11:01.452 --> 11:02.662
You too, Ms. Seong.

11:03.371 --> 11:04.455
[chuckles]

11:06.166 --> 11:08.459
I am deeply honored, Your Majesty.

11:09.627 --> 11:10.837
[guests cheering]
STYLE
::cue()

11:34.360 --> 11:35.361
[♪ music ends]

11:35.862 --> 11:36.863
[owl hoots]

11:41.910 --> 11:43.077
[breathing heavily]

11:47.582 --> 11:48.625
Prime Minister Min.

11:56.299 --> 11:57.634
Utilize your veto power.

11:57.717 --> 11:59.135
Your Majesty.

11:59.219 --> 12:01.596
Royal marriages must be approved
by the prime minister.

12:01.679 --> 12:04.140
His Majesty approved it
with everyone watching.

12:04.224 --> 12:05.516
That is exactly why!

12:08.728 --> 12:10.563
You are the only option we have.

12:19.822 --> 12:21.616
The Crown and the Cabinet

12:23.076 --> 12:24.369
must remain unified.

12:36.756 --> 12:37.799
[exhales deeply]

12:39.676 --> 12:40.718
That's right.

12:40.802 --> 12:43.012
Yes, of course. All right, then.

12:45.640 --> 12:47.433
You must've had quite a day.

12:47.934 --> 12:49.727
Oh. Aide Choi.

12:49.811 --> 12:51.771
Is there usually no cell service here?

12:51.854 --> 12:54.941
Ah. They probably blocked the signal today
because of all the guests.

12:55.024 --> 12:57.819
Ah. Then is there anywhere
with a wired connection?

12:57.902 --> 12:59.112
Wired connection…

12:59.904 --> 13:00.905
Follow me.

13:08.037 --> 13:10.665
Our sincerest congratulations,
Your Royal Highness.

13:12.292 --> 13:13.501
To you as well, Ms. Seong.

13:17.255 --> 13:18.256
[clicks tongue]

14:00.214 --> 14:01.215
Who knew

14:01.924 --> 14:04.010
you had such a gift for deception?

14:05.178 --> 14:07.597
I meant what I said when we spoke earlier.

14:08.890 --> 14:10.308
Though you may not believe me.

14:11.851 --> 14:13.728
Did you think
I would simply let this stand?

14:15.730 --> 14:17.106
And if you do not?

14:19.150 --> 14:22.195
Do you plan to go against
His Majesty's royal command?

14:35.333 --> 14:36.793
Do not be too enraged.

14:38.586 --> 14:40.213
I simply wanted my marriage

14:41.339 --> 14:43.091
to be conducted on my terms.

14:44.842 --> 14:47.178
A grand prince's marriage is hardly
a private matter.

14:47.929 --> 14:49.514
How did someone so well-informed…

14:52.266 --> 14:53.434
ever see fit

14:54.769 --> 14:56.062
to amend my brother's will?

15:09.742 --> 15:11.244
-That is absurd--
-Smile.

15:13.204 --> 15:14.831
There are many eyes on us.

15:28.386 --> 15:29.387
[Huiju] Jeongwoo.

15:31.556 --> 15:32.557
Shall we?
STYLE
::cue()

15:47.029 --> 15:48.656
That ruthless brat never showed up?

15:48.739 --> 15:50.908
Yeah, she's not in her room
or the library either.

15:50.992 --> 15:53.119
I thought the ninth graders
had their exam today.

15:53.202 --> 15:55.538
I guess she won't be
the top laureate this time.

15:55.621 --> 15:56.914
Maybe someone locked her up.

15:56.998 --> 15:59.000
[student 1] You think?
But who would do that?

15:59.083 --> 16:00.334
[student 2] You never know.

16:00.418 --> 16:02.128
She was always early, though.

16:08.050 --> 16:10.761
ELEVATOR OUT OF ORDER

16:10.845 --> 16:12.471
-[panting]
-[pounding on door]

16:12.555 --> 16:13.556
[young Huiju] Hello?

16:14.348 --> 16:16.184
Is anyone out there?

16:16.767 --> 16:18.019
Hello?

16:18.561 --> 16:19.645
Damn it!

16:22.190 --> 16:24.025
-There's someone in here!
-Huiju?

16:25.359 --> 16:26.527
[grunts]

16:28.237 --> 16:29.238
Jeongwoo.

16:29.739 --> 16:32.116
[breathes heavily] Take my hand.

16:34.452 --> 16:35.870
[both grunt]

16:37.872 --> 16:39.290
Are you okay?

16:39.373 --> 16:41.459
[gasps] Come with me.

16:43.794 --> 16:44.962
Where are we going?

16:45.046 --> 16:47.340
-You tell them for me.
-What?

16:47.423 --> 16:50.509
Tell them I'm late
because I was trapped in there.

16:51.385 --> 16:53.054
They'll believe you.

16:53.137 --> 16:54.513
[♪ dreamy music playing]

17:31.634 --> 17:33.219
Are you still against this marriage?

17:36.430 --> 17:37.640
Can't you give me a break?

17:38.641 --> 17:41.310
If I lose you, I'll have no one left.

18:22.268 --> 18:23.311
Promise me.

18:24.395 --> 18:26.022
That you'll never lie to me again.

18:28.399 --> 18:31.027
Then I'll always be on your side.

18:38.576 --> 18:39.577
Okay.

18:40.620 --> 18:41.621
[chuckles]

18:55.801 --> 18:56.802
[Huiju sighs]

18:58.554 --> 18:59.597
[chuckles]

19:00.890 --> 19:02.391
This is Queen UIHYEON's ring, right?

19:03.601 --> 19:05.353
She always wore it.

19:06.228 --> 19:08.648
I saw it when I was a kid,
but I still remember it.

19:09.273 --> 19:10.483
It was just so pretty.

19:13.361 --> 19:16.155
But are you sure
you can just give this to me?

19:16.656 --> 19:17.865
It's your mother's ring.

19:19.450 --> 19:20.660
Of course not.

19:21.285 --> 19:22.953
That is a national treasure.

19:23.037 --> 19:24.413
Return it when we get divorced.

19:26.207 --> 19:27.541
Geez, just take it now.

19:27.625 --> 19:29.460
They've already got plenty of shots of it.

19:29.543 --> 19:30.836
Forget it.

19:31.962 --> 19:33.964
Mother didn't even like that ring.

19:34.799 --> 19:35.800
Why not?

19:37.635 --> 19:38.886
Perhaps it was too heavy?

19:52.191 --> 19:54.443
I guess you were her favorite.

19:56.112 --> 19:58.531
This ring is
a national treasure, after all.
STYLE
::cue()

19:59.490 --> 20:01.158
Yet she passed it down to you.

20:01.242 --> 20:03.411
Not to your brother, the future king.

20:08.874 --> 20:09.875
[scoffs]

20:12.670 --> 20:15.172
That decision left my father furious.

20:17.508 --> 20:18.551
Father…

20:20.136 --> 20:21.679
detested giving me anything.

20:25.766 --> 20:26.892
[sighs]

20:35.818 --> 20:36.944
[clicks tongue]

20:37.027 --> 20:38.154
That's fathers for you.

20:43.576 --> 20:44.618
[chuckles]

20:45.703 --> 20:46.954
[breathes deeply]

20:51.000 --> 20:52.418
[♪ romantic music playing]

21:52.061 --> 21:53.270
[Hyeon] My goodness.

21:54.230 --> 21:56.106
Could you be any prettier?

21:56.190 --> 21:57.525
Do you like roses?

21:58.484 --> 21:59.485
Pardon?

21:59.568 --> 22:01.362
David Austin. Juliet roses.

22:01.445 --> 22:03.072
These are Peony roses.

22:03.155 --> 22:05.199
-They're all roses.
-Huh?

22:05.282 --> 22:07.076
My parents run a flower shop.

22:09.537 --> 22:10.538
Ms. Do,

22:10.621 --> 22:13.082
-are you a flower shop heiress?
-[door opens]

22:13.749 --> 22:14.875
How's the response been?

22:16.043 --> 22:18.128
They're going nuts out there.

22:18.754 --> 22:20.798
Because of the proposal?
Did foreign media pick it up?

22:20.881 --> 22:24.468
-Both domestic and international media.
-Ha. [giggles]

22:24.552 --> 22:26.595
KOREAN PRINCE'S PROPOSAL
BREAKS CLASS BARRIER

22:26.679 --> 22:28.097
I-AN PROPOSES TO SEONG HUIJU

22:29.598 --> 22:30.599
[sighs deeply]

22:31.433 --> 22:33.269
Set up a meeting
with the PR team tomorrow.

22:33.853 --> 22:35.354
I already set it all up.

22:35.437 --> 22:37.147
It's at 10:00 a.m. tomorrow.

22:39.233 --> 22:42.862
Your Royal Highness, can I wear this ring
to my interview tomorrow?

22:45.239 --> 22:47.157
-Do as you wish.
-[giggles]

22:48.117 --> 22:50.035
Look at it. Isn't it so pretty?

22:50.119 --> 22:52.621
-[softly] It's so pretty.
-Look with your eyes, not your hands.

22:55.165 --> 22:56.166
[chuckles]

22:59.295 --> 23:00.296
So pretty.

23:01.755 --> 23:03.299
Wow, this is insane.

23:03.382 --> 23:05.050
He proposed to her?

23:06.051 --> 23:09.138
Babe, we're officially a royal family now!

23:09.221 --> 23:10.806
I know, right?

23:10.890 --> 23:13.225
So I'm officially Grand Prince I-AN's…

23:15.394 --> 23:16.562
brother-in-law now.

23:16.645 --> 23:17.897
That's right.

23:28.449 --> 23:29.450
What's wrong?

23:32.077 --> 23:33.579
Something doesn't feel right.

23:33.662 --> 23:37.541
You just don't like the idea
of Huiju becoming a royal, do you?

23:37.625 --> 23:40.210
No, that's not it.

23:40.294 --> 23:42.588
Babe, she needs to become a royal

23:42.671 --> 23:45.174
for you to become
the sole Castle Group heir.

23:45.966 --> 23:47.384
I know that.

23:48.177 --> 23:49.303
-Then what?
-[stammers]

23:52.139 --> 23:54.183
About that damn mechanic who died.

23:54.266 --> 23:55.976
Don't you think something feels off?

23:58.938 --> 24:01.690
[sucks teeth] You have a point.

24:03.984 --> 24:05.069
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

24:15.496 --> 24:16.747
Announce me.

24:16.830 --> 24:17.957
[Im] Your Majesty.

24:18.832 --> 24:20.751
Lord INPYEONG has arrived.

24:21.669 --> 24:22.795
Show him in.

24:36.725 --> 24:38.018
Nuptials?

24:38.811 --> 24:39.979
This is nonsense.

24:42.022 --> 24:44.316
I will petition His Majesty
to rescind his command.

24:44.400 --> 24:45.442
You will do no such thing.

24:46.610 --> 24:49.238
A royal command that can be overturned
in the blink of an eye

24:50.781 --> 24:52.199
is no command at all.

24:52.783 --> 24:53.784
So?

24:54.618 --> 24:56.453
Will you just accept it?

25:00.416 --> 25:01.625
Grand Prince I-AN…

25:04.086 --> 25:06.046
knows about the late King's dying wish.

25:10.050 --> 25:12.511
You intend for Grand Prince I-AN
to ascend the throne?

25:13.554 --> 25:15.848
Have you truly gone mad?

25:17.266 --> 25:19.101
It will be better than dying.

25:23.439 --> 25:25.232
It would be better to die.

25:29.987 --> 25:31.530
I'd rather see you dead.

25:33.365 --> 25:34.533
[scoffs]

25:41.248 --> 25:43.250
For the sake of the Crown Prince.

25:49.131 --> 25:51.550
It did not appear to be
a remark made in passing.

25:52.926 --> 25:55.345
-You were certain--
-I doubt he has any evidence.

25:59.433 --> 26:00.559
The fire that day…

26:06.065 --> 26:07.775
reduced everything to ashes.

26:10.444 --> 26:11.445
Thus,

26:11.528 --> 26:13.447
I shall accept

26:13.530 --> 26:15.074
that unsavory union.

26:16.533 --> 26:19.244
-Your Majesty.
-As long as he knows about that will,

26:19.787 --> 26:21.789
we can never join forces with him.

26:21.872 --> 26:23.665
-So?
-Seong Huiju.

26:25.667 --> 26:27.586
She will prove to be his weakness.

26:29.213 --> 26:31.465
It would be best to keep her
within arm's reach.

26:32.549 --> 26:34.384
Do you not agree?

26:44.353 --> 26:47.439
A 21ST CENTURY CINDERELLA,
COMMONER TO ROYALTY

26:52.111 --> 26:54.863
I'm not entirely on board either,
but what choice do we have?

26:54.947 --> 26:56.573
He's right, Father.

26:56.657 --> 26:59.576
There was a public proposal,
and His Majesty gave them his blessing.

27:01.787 --> 27:03.080
Oh, right.

27:03.163 --> 27:06.375
Father, maybe we can take this chance
to redistribute the company shares--

27:06.458 --> 27:07.918
Dayeong.

27:08.418 --> 27:09.545
Yes?

27:10.587 --> 27:12.089
I need you to call your parents.

27:12.673 --> 27:14.299
[stutters] My parents?

27:15.092 --> 27:17.469
We need to plant someone in the palace.

27:20.514 --> 27:21.849
Your sister

27:22.808 --> 27:25.519
should have at least one person
she can rely on.

27:27.771 --> 27:32.860
CASTLE BEAUTY

27:45.372 --> 27:46.915
-By the way, Babe.
-Yes?

27:46.999 --> 27:49.459
I thought your father disliked Huiju.

27:50.335 --> 27:53.255
He does dislike her, but he hates it more
when others pick on her.

27:53.881 --> 27:54.882
What?

27:55.424 --> 27:56.842
That's just how he is.

27:56.925 --> 27:58.093
[gasps]

28:00.721 --> 28:02.514
I can't believe I'm seeing it in person.

28:03.557 --> 28:04.808
How many carats is this?

28:06.310 --> 28:08.061
-Seriously? [clicks tongue]
-[grunts]
STYLE
::cue()

28:09.438 --> 28:10.480
Well, anyway…

28:11.315 --> 28:13.692
Have you named your successor yet?

28:15.319 --> 28:16.320
My successor?

28:16.403 --> 28:17.905
Royals can't work.

28:17.988 --> 28:20.574
Then, you know, your company…

28:22.075 --> 28:24.369
You'll need to hand over
your management rights.

28:26.204 --> 28:28.290
-So?
-What do you mean, "So"?

28:28.790 --> 28:30.000
I mean…

28:30.709 --> 28:32.753
This company is your life's work.

28:32.836 --> 28:34.504
This is when family steps up.

28:35.255 --> 28:38.800
You wouldn't want to hand it over
to a complete stranger…

28:39.384 --> 28:40.510
Right?

28:40.594 --> 28:43.055
-Don't you agree, babe?
-Of course. Yes.

28:43.555 --> 28:45.682
Your dear brother will take good--

28:45.766 --> 28:48.810
That is my decision to make.

28:49.394 --> 28:52.481
Did you find out what I asked about?

28:53.273 --> 28:55.317
Talking to you is like
talking to a brick wall.

28:56.985 --> 28:58.695
[sighs] Anyway… [clears throat]

28:59.404 --> 29:00.656
…I did find him.

29:00.739 --> 29:03.742
He went to great lengths to find him.

29:03.825 --> 29:05.160
[Taeju] I know, right?

29:05.243 --> 29:07.663
Listen, it was not easy at all. Nowadays…

29:07.746 --> 29:08.872
Damn it.

29:10.540 --> 29:11.792
She just won't let me talk.

29:13.752 --> 29:14.753
[scoffs]

29:15.504 --> 29:16.546
[clears throat]

29:19.174 --> 29:20.217
He's dead.

29:23.053 --> 29:24.179
What?

29:24.262 --> 29:25.389
He died.

29:25.472 --> 29:28.058
So I dug around a little, just in case,

29:28.141 --> 29:29.434
but I found nothing.

29:30.185 --> 29:31.812
No parents. No siblings.

29:37.609 --> 29:38.777
[exhales sharply]

29:45.158 --> 29:48.954
Listen, you meet all kinds
of crazy people in life.

29:49.037 --> 29:51.915
-For… [bleep] …sake!
-Damn, you scared me.

29:53.166 --> 29:56.128
That… [bleep]
…I should've killed him myself.

29:56.211 --> 29:57.921
But some… [bleep] …asshole beat me to it!

29:59.214 --> 30:01.675
I forgot who you were for a second there.

30:01.758 --> 30:03.176
[knock on door]

30:03.260 --> 30:04.344
[grunting]

30:05.637 --> 30:07.931
That's five minutes.
You need to leave now.

30:08.015 --> 30:09.641
-Us?
-Yes.

30:09.725 --> 30:13.020
Wow, our company nowadays is just…
Nobody knows their place anymore.

30:13.103 --> 30:14.271
-Let's go.
-Okay.

30:16.606 --> 30:17.607
Never again.

30:19.109 --> 30:21.778
Telling me to leave?
I'm a Senior Managing Director, you know.

30:21.862 --> 30:23.030
My apologies.

30:23.113 --> 30:24.114
Take care.

30:27.075 --> 30:28.160
[exhales deeply]

30:36.835 --> 30:39.504
This is the list of anticipated questions.
Take a look.

30:39.588 --> 30:40.589
Okay.

30:42.924 --> 30:43.925
[sighs]

30:45.010 --> 30:48.346
Why are these questions so cliché?

30:48.430 --> 30:51.099
"The Grand Prince's strengths
and weaknesses?"

30:51.641 --> 30:53.185
Who would even care?

30:53.894 --> 30:55.353
It should be more like…

30:55.437 --> 30:56.855
"When was your first kiss?"

30:56.938 --> 30:58.982
"Who wins in a fight behind closed doors?"

30:59.066 --> 31:02.277
Aren't these the sort of questions
they should be asking?

31:02.360 --> 31:05.113
The palace already screened them,
so they had no other choice.

31:05.197 --> 31:06.198
Ah.

31:06.948 --> 31:10.452
I swear, they really need a new PR team.

31:11.119 --> 31:12.162
Tsk, tsk, tsk.

31:13.622 --> 31:15.540
How did you two meet?

31:15.624 --> 31:17.042
Our first meeting?

31:18.251 --> 31:19.252
Mmm…

31:22.964 --> 31:24.925
[chuckles] It was quite a long time ago.

31:25.550 --> 31:27.344
We went to the same school.

31:27.427 --> 31:30.055
Were you just strictly classmates
back then?

31:30.138 --> 31:31.306
No romantic feelings?

31:32.140 --> 31:35.185
And Your Royal Highness?
You are here too, are you not?

31:35.268 --> 31:37.020
Will you receive demerit points as well?

31:37.104 --> 31:38.146
[chuckles]

31:39.773 --> 31:41.691
Sparks flew back then as well.

31:42.400 --> 31:45.237
But nothing ever happened
between us back then.

31:45.320 --> 31:46.321
It just felt like…

31:47.155 --> 31:48.990
we came from two very different worlds.

31:49.074 --> 31:51.785
From when you were
just acquaintances to now,

31:51.868 --> 31:53.787
what would you say is the biggest change?

31:57.958 --> 31:59.292
Hmm…

32:01.461 --> 32:03.046
Being overprotective?

32:03.130 --> 32:04.131
Seong Huiju!

32:06.466 --> 32:08.468
She will be staying here
for the time being.
STYLE
::cue()

32:12.347 --> 32:14.015
I am trying to protect you!

32:18.103 --> 32:20.438
He must think that I'd break
at the lightest touch.

32:22.190 --> 32:23.316
As if I were made of glass.

32:27.070 --> 32:28.864
[both laugh]

32:30.407 --> 32:31.408
"Glass."

32:33.493 --> 32:36.079
Why? Do I seem unbreakable to you?

32:38.957 --> 32:39.958
Just kidding.

32:40.542 --> 32:41.626
[giggles]

32:55.056 --> 32:56.057
[sighs]

33:00.729 --> 33:02.272
[sighs]

33:02.355 --> 33:03.356
[Hyeon] Your Royal Highness.

33:03.940 --> 33:05.942
Why don't you take a break
and look at this?

33:06.026 --> 33:07.360
What is it?

33:07.444 --> 33:11.323
This is the draft
of Ms. Seong's interview.

33:16.077 --> 33:17.662
A CHAT WITH SEONG HUIJU,
CEO OF CASTLE BEAUTY

33:17.746 --> 33:18.788
[I-AN scoffs]

33:18.872 --> 33:19.956
[♪ pop music playing]

33:31.843 --> 33:34.429
Steward Kim, Her Ladyship is here!

33:39.809 --> 33:40.894
Goodness me!

33:41.519 --> 33:43.188
Your Ladyship!

33:52.447 --> 33:54.366
You act like it's been years.

33:54.449 --> 33:55.784
I know, right?

33:55.867 --> 33:58.912
At this rate, another lovers' quarrel
will be the death of me.

33:58.995 --> 34:01.498
As if you didn't snatch the hopae
from my hands.

34:01.581 --> 34:02.499
[stammers]

34:03.083 --> 34:04.417
[Youngseon] Why is Ms. Do here?

34:05.252 --> 34:06.419
She's my right-hand woman.

34:08.004 --> 34:09.464
[chuckles]

34:09.547 --> 34:10.757
Let's go inside.

34:10.840 --> 34:11.841
[chuckling] Yes, ma'am.

34:15.095 --> 34:16.096
What?

34:16.638 --> 34:17.639
[sighs]

34:18.765 --> 34:21.226
I asked for those files ages ago and yet…

34:23.061 --> 34:24.062
Wow.

34:24.145 --> 34:25.563
Let me call you back.

34:29.859 --> 34:30.902
Do you like it?

34:32.028 --> 34:35.073
Oh… It's just so pretty.

34:35.907 --> 34:36.908
[door opens]

34:39.369 --> 34:41.663
You can go now.
I'll take care of the rest.

34:42.580 --> 34:44.040
No, it'll only take a second…

34:47.085 --> 34:49.629
Very well. Please let me know
if you need anything.

34:58.054 --> 34:59.556
[I-AN] Return to my private residence.

35:01.099 --> 35:02.100
What?

35:02.642 --> 35:03.685
[scoffs]

35:03.768 --> 35:07.272
Am I someone who shows up
and leaves on your command?

35:07.355 --> 35:08.773
We'll start packing immediately.

35:09.649 --> 35:10.692
Ms. Do.

35:10.775 --> 35:12.485
I'm worried about leaving you alone.

35:12.569 --> 35:14.779
At least you'll be safe there
with the Royal Guard.

35:15.864 --> 35:17.407
-Right?
-Of course.

35:17.490 --> 35:19.743
Our Royal Guard is top-notch.

35:19.826 --> 35:21.328
[I-AN] One more thing.

35:21.411 --> 35:23.163
Please go ahead, Your Royal Highness.

35:23.246 --> 35:24.998
There's a spy at my private residence.

35:25.665 --> 35:26.666
A spy?

35:27.250 --> 35:28.918
Is it someone on your staff?

35:29.002 --> 35:29.878
Do you have a name?

35:32.672 --> 35:33.882
Just a moment.

35:34.382 --> 35:36.009
[♪ tense music playing]

35:38.261 --> 35:40.180
PERSONAL DETAILS REPORT
LEE AREUM

35:40.263 --> 35:41.264
Oh?

35:42.015 --> 35:43.099
[scoffs]

35:43.183 --> 35:45.018
Any chance of wiretaps or hidden cameras?

35:45.101 --> 35:46.102
That's impossible.

35:46.186 --> 35:48.813
Both the palace and private residence
are checked regularly.

35:48.897 --> 35:52.359
Then that means she only reports
what she can see and hear.

35:53.318 --> 35:56.613
How many times
have I told you to just kick her out?

35:56.696 --> 35:58.740
She'll only be replaced by someone else.

36:00.408 --> 36:01.743
I'll move in with you.

36:02.619 --> 36:03.620
You will?

36:03.703 --> 36:04.829
Yes.

36:07.165 --> 36:08.166
Would that be okay?

36:12.504 --> 36:13.505
As you wish.
STYLE
::cue()

36:16.466 --> 36:18.009
[phone buzzing]

36:18.677 --> 36:20.512
Ms. Do, I need to take this.

36:27.852 --> 36:28.853
Yes, Your Royal Highness.

36:30.647 --> 36:31.648
The palace, tomorrow?

36:32.857 --> 36:34.234
We need to plan the wedding.

36:35.485 --> 36:37.362
I'll have a car sent for you.

36:38.488 --> 36:39.656
Don't drive yourself.

36:41.825 --> 36:42.826
[call disconnects]

36:42.909 --> 36:43.868
[chuckles]

36:43.952 --> 36:44.953
[♪ piano music playing]

37:03.054 --> 37:04.055
[Jeongwoo] Huiju.

37:05.348 --> 37:06.349
Jeongwoo!

37:08.685 --> 37:09.686
[chuckles]

37:12.230 --> 37:15.150
But are you going to help us
plan the wedding too?

37:15.233 --> 37:16.151
You didn't think I would?

37:16.234 --> 37:19.487
I'm the prime minister, and your wedding
is basically a state affair.

37:20.363 --> 37:21.364
That's true.

37:24.701 --> 37:27.412
[Lady Choi] Your Royal Highness,
Ms. Seong has arrived.

37:30.749 --> 37:31.750
[clears throat]

37:33.793 --> 37:35.962
[Lady Choi] Prime Minister Min
is here as well.

37:38.173 --> 37:39.174
[clears throat]

37:40.008 --> 37:41.009
Show them in.

37:43.470 --> 37:44.471
[sighs]

37:59.944 --> 38:01.321
Did the two of you…

38:03.740 --> 38:04.949
come here together?

38:05.617 --> 38:06.618
No.

38:07.577 --> 38:08.787
We met at the palace gates.

38:09.829 --> 38:10.830
I see.

38:13.833 --> 38:15.084
Now then,

38:15.668 --> 38:16.669
shall we get started?

38:22.091 --> 38:24.219
Can we push back the meeting a bit?

38:25.094 --> 38:26.679
Yeah. Around two hours?

38:28.515 --> 38:30.475
-This is taking longer than expected.
-Ms. Do!

38:31.267 --> 38:32.268
[♪ whimsical music playing]

38:32.352 --> 38:33.603
[Hyejeong] Okay, thank you.

38:35.647 --> 38:37.440
You must be here with Ms. Seong.

38:37.524 --> 38:38.817
-Yes.
-I see.

38:39.901 --> 38:42.278
Did you see the flowers on the way in?

38:42.362 --> 38:45.406
The palace becomes
a flower paradise this time of year.

38:45.490 --> 38:46.950
-Especially…
-Hmm?

38:47.992 --> 38:49.786
-Ms. Do?
-Yes?

38:49.869 --> 38:53.206
The lilies and hydrangeas
are especially magnificent.

38:53.289 --> 38:54.415
If you're free later…

38:54.499 --> 38:55.667
[Lady Choi clearing throat]

38:56.292 --> 38:57.502
Hydrangeas?

38:59.546 --> 39:00.797
[chuckles]

39:01.339 --> 39:02.340
[clears throat]

39:02.924 --> 39:03.925
See you.

39:08.888 --> 39:13.184
Your royal wedding will be held on a scale
comparable to the Crown Prince's.

39:14.060 --> 39:15.228
[I-AN] For what reason?

39:15.311 --> 39:16.938
The royal family has seen many tragedies.

39:17.021 --> 39:18.940
The people suffered just as much.

39:19.023 --> 39:20.900
Thus, we must take this chance

39:20.984 --> 39:24.070
to remind the public that the Crown
still stands strong.

39:24.153 --> 39:26.322
-That will--
-Make the Crown more useful.

39:27.407 --> 39:29.909
Both at home and abroad.

39:31.953 --> 39:33.454
[chuckles] That's right.

39:33.538 --> 39:35.331
There are notable economic benefits too.

39:36.875 --> 39:40.295
Royal weddings generate more revenue
than they cost, after all.
STYLE
::cue()

39:40.378 --> 39:41.629
How much does it cost?

39:42.463 --> 39:43.464
Around…

39:45.550 --> 39:46.759
[♪ whimsical music playing]

39:46.843 --> 39:48.261
[coughs] So hot!

39:48.344 --> 39:49.762
Are you okay? Did you burn your tongue?

39:50.388 --> 39:51.556
No, I'm fine.

39:53.266 --> 39:54.309
Wait, hold on.

39:55.018 --> 39:57.520
What kind of revenue
could justify that cost?

39:58.146 --> 39:59.272
Prime Minister Min.

40:01.816 --> 40:04.027
Seong Huiju will soon become my wife.

40:04.944 --> 40:06.279
Please mind your conduct.

40:11.868 --> 40:12.869
[chuckles]

40:16.080 --> 40:17.916
You do not need
to keep up appearances with me.

40:19.083 --> 40:20.001
[Huiju] Oh…

40:21.044 --> 40:22.670
You see… [chuckles]

40:24.464 --> 40:26.174
Jeongwoo knows everything.

40:27.967 --> 40:28.968
[laughs]

40:32.889 --> 40:33.890
[scoffs]

40:38.436 --> 40:39.437
[sighs]

40:39.938 --> 40:42.065
Until your divorce is finalized
without incident…

40:45.526 --> 40:48.905
I will do my best to assist you both.

40:53.409 --> 40:54.410
Yay!

40:58.414 --> 40:59.457
[chuckles]

41:02.585 --> 41:03.586
[clears throat]

41:04.253 --> 41:06.714
Your father seemed pleased, didn't he?

41:06.798 --> 41:07.757
[chuckles]

41:07.840 --> 41:08.841
Of course.

41:08.925 --> 41:11.719
Who would ever be against their in-laws
securing royal ties?

41:12.720 --> 41:14.430
Wait, that's why he was pleased?

41:14.514 --> 41:16.849
Not because I'm going
to inherit Castle Group?

41:16.933 --> 41:18.893
-[car approaching]
-We can't be sure of that just yet.

41:19.394 --> 41:20.395
What?

41:20.937 --> 41:23.022
Wait, what's that supposed to mean?

41:23.106 --> 41:23.940
Han Dayeong.

41:26.859 --> 41:28.361
What's that brat doing here?

41:28.861 --> 41:31.072
-Uh, hello.
-Babe, shoulders back.

41:31.948 --> 41:32.782
[chuckles]

41:33.866 --> 41:35.034
Here to see your parents?

41:35.118 --> 41:38.788
Yeah, my father wanted to give
my sister-in-law a wedding gift.

41:39.622 --> 41:41.708
I assume you saw the news?

41:43.459 --> 41:45.461
I thought you weren't close
to your sister.

41:46.129 --> 41:47.964
-Well, you know, family can be…
-[Dayeong chuckles]

41:48.923 --> 41:52.343
What are you talking about?
They're basically inseparable.

41:53.511 --> 41:54.637
Uh, yes, we're close.

41:55.596 --> 41:58.850
-Really?
-She also leans on me so much.

41:59.350 --> 42:01.769
I'm wondering if I should
join her in the palace.

42:01.853 --> 42:02.979
-You?
-You?

42:05.148 --> 42:06.190
Yeah.

42:06.816 --> 42:09.068
It's not like she has a mother to lean on.

42:09.819 --> 42:12.405
I have to step in. What choice do I have?

42:14.073 --> 42:15.700
She has no other choice…

42:16.826 --> 42:20.747
I swear I had no choice. He walked in
when I was talking to Ms. Do--

42:20.830 --> 42:22.415
You call that an excuse?

42:23.499 --> 42:25.209
That's just what happened.

42:27.295 --> 42:28.463
I'm sorry.

42:30.882 --> 42:32.008
[sighs]

42:32.091 --> 42:33.843
But it's not all so bad, is it?

42:34.594 --> 42:36.763
-What?
-We need the approval

42:36.846 --> 42:39.432
of the royal family and the Cabinet
for every little thing.

42:39.515 --> 42:41.893
With Jeongwoo on our side,

42:41.976 --> 42:44.520
we don't need to worry
about the Cabinet anymore.

42:44.604 --> 42:46.022
How are you so sure?

42:46.105 --> 42:47.857
-What?
-About Prime Minister Min.

42:49.150 --> 42:51.486
How can you be sure
he'll always take our side?

42:51.569 --> 42:52.612
Because, obviously…

42:52.695 --> 42:53.821
That's a bit too naïve, no?

42:54.447 --> 42:55.364
Excuse me?

42:55.448 --> 43:01.788
A businesswoman should know better
than to trust people so easily, no?

43:06.292 --> 43:07.293
[sighs]
STYLE
::cue()

43:08.503 --> 43:11.631
Your Royal Highness
and I only started getting in sync.

43:12.256 --> 43:15.093
Then it would make more sense
for me to trust him over you, no?

43:15.718 --> 43:18.012
He's always been on my side
since we were kids.

43:18.096 --> 43:20.056
-What?
-Let's face it.

43:20.139 --> 43:23.226
For all I know,
you could just bail out on me again.

43:24.018 --> 43:26.062
Calling you fickle
would be an understatement.

43:26.145 --> 43:27.313
[scoffs]

43:27.396 --> 43:29.065
"Fi… Fickle"?

43:29.148 --> 43:32.693
Just know that
I really want to draw up a contract,

43:32.777 --> 43:34.362
but I'm doing my best to hold back.

43:35.738 --> 43:37.740
[scoffs, laughs]

43:39.617 --> 43:40.701
Draw it up.

43:41.786 --> 43:42.954
-What?
-Draw it up.

43:43.037 --> 43:44.497
-Draw it up?
-Draw it up.

43:45.915 --> 43:47.083
Let's draw it up!

43:55.299 --> 43:57.385
[♪ fiery music playing]

43:59.262 --> 44:00.805
So we will divorce…

44:00.888 --> 44:02.181
Within three years at the latest.

44:02.265 --> 44:04.183
The sooner, the better.

44:04.267 --> 44:05.268
[scoffs]

44:05.810 --> 44:08.729
-Post-divorce asset division?
-Aside from the clothes on your back,

44:08.813 --> 44:11.858
any real estate or assets
bestowed by virtue of royal status

44:11.941 --> 44:13.234
must be relinquished.

44:13.317 --> 44:14.277
[scoffs]

44:14.986 --> 44:16.195
Might as well fight over pennies.

44:16.279 --> 44:17.613
"Pennies"?

44:19.073 --> 44:20.283
Very well, then.

44:20.867 --> 44:23.911
However, I will not be relinquishing
my title or rank.

44:23.995 --> 44:26.414
The privileges attached to them
shall also be maintained.

44:26.998 --> 44:29.709
-For life.
-As long as you do not cause

44:29.792 --> 44:32.628
public controversy or violate the law,
you shall retain them.

44:34.422 --> 44:35.423
[scoffs]

44:37.800 --> 44:38.968
There's more.

44:40.386 --> 44:41.387
One.

44:41.971 --> 44:42.972
[sighs]

44:43.055 --> 44:45.308
All matters concerning the palace
shall remain confidential,

44:45.391 --> 44:46.851
during the marriage and thereafter.

44:46.934 --> 44:47.935
Two.

44:48.436 --> 44:50.813
All matters between us
shall remain confidential,

44:50.897 --> 44:52.356
during the marriage and thereafter.

44:52.440 --> 44:54.192
-Three.
-All matters shall

44:54.859 --> 44:56.068
remain confidential.

44:58.070 --> 44:59.197
I hear you.

45:00.114 --> 45:02.783
-In turn, Your Royal Highness--
-If secrecy proves difficult,

45:03.826 --> 45:04.952
just forget it happened.

45:05.494 --> 45:07.121
[♪ somber music playing]

45:07.205 --> 45:08.414
It's all pretend anyway.

45:09.498 --> 45:10.541
It won't matter.

45:20.760 --> 45:24.222
Your Royal Highness,
the Queen Mother has arrived.

45:31.437 --> 45:32.772
[Lady Choi] Your Royal Highness.

45:33.522 --> 45:34.649
[sighs]

45:37.735 --> 45:38.736
[clears throat]

45:45.284 --> 45:46.369
Escort her in.

46:05.471 --> 46:06.514
Your Majesty.

46:07.014 --> 46:08.432
I am Huiju of the Seong Family.

46:11.435 --> 46:12.436
[door closes]

46:14.689 --> 46:17.066
I stopped by
after hearing you were both here.

46:17.149 --> 46:20.027
I wanted to ask
if you two would join me for dinner.

46:20.861 --> 46:24.156
We are soon to be family, after all.

46:29.287 --> 46:30.288
[chuckles]
STYLE
::cue()

46:36.669 --> 46:38.796
-Enjoy.
-You too.

46:46.846 --> 46:49.682
Will Ms. Seong be okay?
What if she gets indigestion?

46:49.765 --> 46:51.934
She'll be fine. She has an iron stomach.

46:52.018 --> 46:53.352
No, you see…

46:53.436 --> 46:54.854
The Queen Mother can be…

46:56.147 --> 46:58.274
a bit old-school.
She can be super intense.

46:58.357 --> 46:59.900
It's fine.

46:59.984 --> 47:01.902
Ms. Seong is quite the rebel too.

47:03.070 --> 47:04.071
I see.

47:04.155 --> 47:06.407
So stop worrying and eat already.

47:06.490 --> 47:09.118
Our bosses will be on edge
after their dinner.

47:11.245 --> 47:12.371
All right then.

47:12.955 --> 47:16.667
Truth be told, I was worried
they might really fall for one another.

47:16.751 --> 47:20.671
I mean, come on.
Who wouldn't fall for Our Royal Highness?

47:20.755 --> 47:22.673
With that face and figure,
and those shoulders like…

47:22.757 --> 47:23.758
Nothing to worry about.

47:23.841 --> 47:25.843
Ms. Seong likes trophy men.

47:26.886 --> 47:27.887
What did you say?

47:27.970 --> 47:29.013
Trophy men.

47:29.096 --> 47:31.265
Ones that show up and leave on command.

47:31.349 --> 47:32.475
Spineless men.

47:33.267 --> 47:35.102
So just eat your food.

47:35.186 --> 47:37.855
The chances of a man
who's summoned people his whole life

47:37.938 --> 47:40.775
and a woman
who's bossed people around her whole life

47:40.858 --> 47:43.486
falling for each other are basically nil.

47:48.657 --> 47:50.242
-What about you, Ms. Hyejeong?
-What?

47:54.205 --> 47:56.624
What's your type?

47:56.707 --> 47:57.708
[♪ soft piano music playing]

48:03.923 --> 48:04.924
[chuckles]

48:07.218 --> 48:08.219
[Hyeon clears throat]

48:09.095 --> 48:12.264
They really know how to cook
their wild greens here.

48:12.348 --> 48:13.516
Kudos, Auntie.

48:37.206 --> 48:39.792
I do hope the food is to your taste.

48:41.168 --> 48:43.254
Thank you, Your Majesty.

48:46.841 --> 48:48.259
This liquor is made from pears.

48:50.010 --> 48:51.470
It is quite strong.

48:51.554 --> 48:52.847
Ah.

48:52.930 --> 48:53.848
Queen Mother.

48:54.807 --> 48:55.808
She…

48:56.475 --> 48:57.977
Can you not handle your alcohol?

48:58.561 --> 49:00.980
I certainly can.

49:01.063 --> 49:02.064
[chuckles]

49:09.029 --> 49:10.489
[♪ tense music playing]

49:16.745 --> 49:18.247
[Huiju, Yun chuckling]

49:20.082 --> 49:21.834
Wait, were you really scolded that much?

49:23.919 --> 49:26.547
He wrote letters of apology so frequently.

49:26.630 --> 49:28.841
I am sure there were enough
to make a whole book.

49:29.425 --> 49:30.759
Is that so?

49:30.843 --> 49:33.304
I guess you were quite the troublemaker.

49:34.597 --> 49:35.639
Drink some water.

49:35.723 --> 49:37.933
Hold on. You're blushing.

49:38.017 --> 49:39.560
You're totally blushing.

49:40.144 --> 49:41.854
[gasps] Your face is red.

49:43.981 --> 49:46.567
If His Majesty, your father,
had still been with us…

49:50.696 --> 49:53.657
I wonder what he would have said
about this union.

49:55.826 --> 49:57.578
[♪ emotional piano music playing]

50:01.415 --> 50:02.416
Queen Mother.

50:08.130 --> 50:09.507
[chuckles]

50:12.134 --> 50:14.637
He would have requested
a letter of apology.

50:15.763 --> 50:19.183
He so frequently scolded you
for standing in your brother's way.

50:19.725 --> 50:23.896
Surely, he would not have approved
of you standing in your nephew's way.

50:24.897 --> 50:26.065
You should stop there.

50:32.321 --> 50:34.365
Can you truly claim to be wholly innocent

50:35.658 --> 50:38.160
in the death of the late King?

50:43.290 --> 50:45.876
What goes through your mind
when you look at His Majesty?

50:47.086 --> 50:48.629
Do you wish to stand in his way

50:49.171 --> 50:51.882
and eliminate him,
just as you did the late King?

51:07.273 --> 51:08.315
Are you okay?
STYLE
::cue()

51:18.576 --> 51:20.202
Do you know why he was given

51:21.620 --> 51:23.497
the royal title of "I-AN"?

51:27.459 --> 51:28.919
"I" as in "rule."

51:29.503 --> 51:30.796
"AN" as in "peace."

51:32.214 --> 51:33.966
It calls upon him to refrain

51:35.676 --> 51:37.595
from harming the stability of the Crown.

51:56.822 --> 51:59.241
Please excuse us now.

52:08.584 --> 52:12.338
It will soon be time
to close the palace gates.

52:12.963 --> 52:13.964
[chuckles]

52:21.347 --> 52:22.473
[♪ music ends]

52:26.477 --> 52:27.561
Slow down.

52:31.106 --> 52:32.441
I said, slow down.

52:34.568 --> 52:37.780
Just know I'm holding back
because we're not married yet.

52:38.364 --> 52:40.032
You keep saying you're holding back.

52:40.115 --> 52:43.202
If I had it my way,
the Queen Mother would be pulverized--

52:43.285 --> 52:44.286
Whoa!

52:46.205 --> 52:47.206
[sighs]

52:53.504 --> 52:54.588
Just hang in there.

52:55.923 --> 52:57.383
As soon as we're married,

52:57.466 --> 53:01.470
I will clear everything
that stands in your way.

53:02.388 --> 53:03.806
[♪ soft piano music playing]

53:10.020 --> 53:11.021
[chuckles]

53:13.732 --> 53:15.025
You don't believe me?

53:17.277 --> 53:18.278
I do.

53:19.697 --> 53:22.533
So get me out of here.

53:23.534 --> 53:24.535
What?

53:26.662 --> 53:28.330
I don't want to sleep here tonight.

53:58.152 --> 53:59.570
Should you be driving right now?

54:00.779 --> 54:02.781
Leaving the palace was defiance in itself.

54:04.616 --> 54:05.784
Aren't you scared?

54:07.202 --> 54:08.912
The accident wasn't too long ago.

54:11.540 --> 54:12.624
I like driving.

54:21.300 --> 54:22.426
It feels like flying.

54:23.427 --> 54:24.428
And I can go fast.

54:27.598 --> 54:29.850
I'm not allowed to run or ride a bike.

54:30.476 --> 54:31.769
But I'm allowed to drive.

54:33.395 --> 54:34.813
I don't understand the logic.

54:40.277 --> 54:41.528
[♪ emotional music continues]

54:41.612 --> 54:42.613
[sighs]

54:51.914 --> 54:53.665
Do you want to fly for real?

55:07.429 --> 55:08.764
[♪ music crescendos]

55:12.851 --> 55:13.852
[chuckles]

55:18.607 --> 55:20.192
Do you intend to propose to me?

55:21.485 --> 55:23.820
You've watched way too many dramas.

55:23.904 --> 55:25.405
Then why are we here?

55:26.031 --> 55:27.157
Did you rent this?

55:27.241 --> 55:28.283
It's mine.

55:31.161 --> 55:34.748
So what? You want me to fly here?

55:35.541 --> 55:37.209
You obviously can't fly here.

55:37.292 --> 55:41.129
We can fly right over there.

55:42.172 --> 55:43.173
[chuckles]

55:43.257 --> 55:44.216
Wait here.

55:51.890 --> 55:52.891
Seong Huiju.
STYLE
::cue()

55:57.688 --> 55:59.898
You should not run, Your Majesty!

55:59.982 --> 56:01.191
Your Majesty!

56:01.275 --> 56:02.317
[pants]

56:02.401 --> 56:03.402
Your Majesty!

56:05.237 --> 56:07.489
I dried these myself, Ms. Do.

56:08.490 --> 56:09.491
[slurps]

56:09.575 --> 56:10.867
How is it?

56:10.951 --> 56:12.452
-It's nice.
-I knew it!

56:12.536 --> 56:14.496
I don't offer this to just anyone.

56:14.580 --> 56:15.581
[chuckles]

56:16.331 --> 56:17.666
But I had some yesterday.

56:18.667 --> 56:20.085
-Don't you have work to do?
-Mmm.

56:22.838 --> 56:23.797
Uncle!

56:23.880 --> 56:25.424
-Your Majesty.
-Oh, Your Majesty.

56:28.010 --> 56:29.970
Oh, uh, is it just you here?

56:30.554 --> 56:31.680
Yes, Your Majesty.

56:31.763 --> 56:32.848
Where is Uncle?

56:32.931 --> 56:36.393
I heard Ms. Seong was here as well.

56:36.476 --> 56:39.104
Oh, we are also wondering
where they could be--

56:39.187 --> 56:40.606
You can just tell me, Your Majesty.

56:40.689 --> 56:42.733
I will be sure to pass along any message.

56:43.859 --> 56:45.193
No need.

56:46.612 --> 56:47.738
[sighs]

56:47.821 --> 56:49.823
-Your Majesty.
-A mighty sigh from His Majesty…

56:49.906 --> 56:51.408
Your Majesty, what is the matter?

56:52.242 --> 56:53.285
He's so cute.

57:07.090 --> 57:08.175
Is someone chasing you?

57:08.759 --> 57:09.843
Why is no one here?

57:10.385 --> 57:12.179
I asked them to clear out.

57:12.763 --> 57:13.805
Can I get you anything?

57:15.557 --> 57:17.893
"A royal can only eat
in verified restaurants."

57:19.728 --> 57:21.146
Wh-- What are you doing?

57:21.229 --> 57:23.065
Just do whatever you want today.

57:24.316 --> 57:26.193
-What?
-I told you it's just us here.

57:27.402 --> 57:30.656
-But a royal--
-Royals never marry commoners.

57:30.739 --> 57:31.948
So why are you marrying me?

57:42.417 --> 57:44.336
[♪ sprightly piano music playing]

57:56.848 --> 57:57.849
[chuckles]

57:58.809 --> 57:59.810
[I-AN exhales loudly]

58:03.146 --> 58:04.648
My goodness.

58:05.774 --> 58:06.983
Are you okay?

58:07.484 --> 58:10.320
-Who gets seasick on a yacht?
-It's just indigestion.

58:10.904 --> 58:11.905
It's indigestion.

58:14.241 --> 58:15.242
[laughing]

58:15.325 --> 58:16.326
[coughs]

58:18.995 --> 58:21.039
I mean, I could prick your finger for you.

58:21.665 --> 58:23.875
-What?
-There should be a needle somewhere.

58:25.085 --> 58:27.003
-A royal…
-Are you scared?

58:27.087 --> 58:30.507
Because a prick would hurt so much?
Shaking in your boots?

58:30.590 --> 58:32.134
[chuckles]

58:33.135 --> 58:35.137
Fine. Let's do it.

58:40.225 --> 58:42.644
Are you sure this works?
Not just a placebo effect?

58:44.187 --> 58:45.230
Ouch!

58:45.897 --> 58:47.065
[sighs]

58:50.444 --> 58:51.695
I feel all better now.

58:51.778 --> 58:52.696
Ouch!

58:54.865 --> 58:57.200
How did I ever put my trust
in such a cowardly prince?

58:57.284 --> 58:59.077
[scoffs] "Cowardly"?

58:59.161 --> 59:00.162
I am…

59:01.413 --> 59:03.749
just not familiar with home remedies.

59:03.832 --> 59:04.875
Let's go now.

59:06.376 --> 59:07.544
Go on.

59:07.627 --> 59:09.755
I told you I'd let you experience flying.

59:11.548 --> 59:12.549
-Come on.
-Wha--
STYLE
::cue()

59:27.063 --> 59:28.106
[inhales deeply]

59:30.066 --> 59:31.067
[giggles]

59:32.486 --> 59:33.487
[I-AN] Oh!

59:35.489 --> 59:36.490
[gasps]

59:36.573 --> 59:38.909
This is too dangerous. Come down now.

59:38.992 --> 59:39.993
Here.

59:40.494 --> 59:41.578
Hold me tight.

59:45.373 --> 59:46.583
[♪ romantic music playing]

59:48.752 --> 59:49.920
[both chuckle]

59:56.009 --> 59:57.010
[sighs]

01:00:05.977 --> 01:00:06.978
[laughs]

01:00:07.938 --> 01:00:08.939
[chuckles]

01:00:11.316 --> 01:00:13.318
[♪ pop ballad playing]

01:01:03.034 --> 01:01:04.369
You said you'd let me fly.

01:01:04.995 --> 01:01:06.413
Why are you the one flying?

01:01:08.164 --> 01:01:10.125
Let's switch. I can hold you.

01:01:10.792 --> 01:01:12.878
-Forget it.
-Why not? Come on…

01:01:12.961 --> 01:01:14.880
-[yelps]
-[grunts]

01:01:14.963 --> 01:01:16.339
[♪ music ends]

01:01:16.423 --> 01:01:17.674
[gasps]

01:01:19.926 --> 01:01:20.927
[sighs]

01:01:21.845 --> 01:01:22.846
[sighs]

01:01:25.974 --> 01:01:27.934
-[grunts]
-[gasps]

01:01:37.110 --> 01:01:38.111
Your Royal Highness.

01:01:38.612 --> 01:01:40.488
Are you hurt anywhere?

01:01:46.912 --> 01:01:48.580
You said I can do whatever I want.

01:01:52.459 --> 01:01:54.252
[♪ romantic music playing]

01:02:01.718 --> 01:02:02.928
[♪ soft piano playing]

01:02:31.790 --> 01:02:32.999
[♪ orchestral strings playing]
STYLE
::cue()

01:03:07.742 --> 01:03:10.620
EPILOGUE

01:03:10.704 --> 01:03:12.122
[sighs]

01:03:12.205 --> 01:03:14.082
You'll be attending
the second half, right?

01:03:16.376 --> 01:03:17.585
Probably.

01:03:19.212 --> 01:03:20.714
I assume you can waltz?

01:03:20.797 --> 01:03:21.840
[chuckles]

01:03:22.674 --> 01:03:23.675
Can you?

01:03:24.300 --> 01:03:25.635
[scoffs, chuckles]

01:03:27.554 --> 01:03:29.973
[♪ piano flourish plays]

01:03:30.056 --> 01:03:32.517
I am a top laureate through and through.

01:03:36.438 --> 01:03:39.274
[♪ piano flourish plays]

01:03:52.537 --> 01:03:54.205
[♪ piano waltz music playing]

01:03:59.044 --> 01:04:00.170
[laughing]

01:04:06.509 --> 01:04:07.635
[chuckles]

01:04:13.600 --> 01:04:14.768
-[exclaims]
-[laughs]

01:04:15.435 --> 01:04:16.478
Let's not do that.

01:04:17.896 --> 01:04:19.064
Hold me up like this.

01:04:19.147 --> 01:04:20.356
Here I come.

01:04:28.073 --> 01:04:29.157
[chuckles]

01:04:32.285 --> 01:04:35.205
PERFECT CROWN

01:04:37.499 --> 01:04:39.000
[♪ upbeat pop song playing]

01:05:13.618 --> 01:05:15.495
We were just caught up in the moment.

01:05:15.578 --> 01:05:18.081
I mean, it's not like
I threw myself at him.

01:05:18.164 --> 01:05:20.166
[groans] Why did I do that?

01:05:20.250 --> 01:05:21.209
Not for me.

01:05:21.292 --> 01:05:23.837
I didn't do it just because
I was caught up in the moment.

01:05:24.504 --> 01:05:26.256
I did it because it's you.

01:05:27.382 --> 01:05:30.176
[Hyejeong] Don't you think it's excessive?
Maybe they're falling for each other.

01:05:30.260 --> 01:05:33.596
I mean, they actually look like
they just started dating.

01:05:34.347 --> 01:05:36.766
[I-AN] Something bothering you?
You've been acting strange.

01:05:36.850 --> 01:05:39.144
[Huiju] You're being
unnecessarily sweet to me.

01:05:40.228 --> 01:05:41.437
I shall wait.

01:05:41.521 --> 01:05:44.232
[Yun] Until the day
you can no longer restrain yourself.

01:05:44.816 --> 01:05:46.901
[I-AN] Restraint always followed desire.

01:05:46.985 --> 01:05:48.444
But it's not easy this time.

01:05:48.528 --> 01:05:51.489
[Huiju] By chance,
do you have feelings for me?

01:05:52.824 --> 01:05:54.826
Translated by Justin S. Kim

01:06:06.129 --> 01:06:09.841
PERFECT CROWN
